    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-11-22T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-11-22T19:00:00-05:00" n="952"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d952">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">661.9331/11–1946: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davis</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-11-22T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 22, 1946—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2131. Your recent message re Sinkiang (2271, Nov 19) not clear Dept, particularly
                    phrase “rejected and preempted by him in that he has already offered concessions
                    to Soviets that do involve political sovereignty”. Who has offered concessions
                    and do you know what they are?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
